## MCP Tools

mtix exposes tools via MCP (Model Context Protocol). Use the `mcp__mtix__` prefixed tools when available — they are preferred over CLI commands:

| Tool | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `mcp__mtix__mtix_context` | **MANDATORY** — assemble full context chain before any work |
| `mcp__mtix__mtix_ready` | Find available work |
| `mcp__mtix__mtix_claim` | Claim a node |
| `mcp__mtix__mtix_done` | Mark work complete |
| `mcp__mtix__mtix_show` | View node details |
| `mcp__mtix__mtix_create` | Create a new node |
| `mcp__mtix__mtix_decompose` | Batch create children |
| `mcp__mtix__mtix_update` | Update node fields |
| `mcp__mtix__mtix_search` | Full-text search |
| `mcp__mtix__mtix_comment` | Add traceability comment |
| `mcp__mtix__mtix_session_start` | Start work session |
| `mcp__mtix__mtix_session_end` | End work session |
| `mcp__mtix__mtix_agent_heartbeat` | Send heartbeat (every 5 min) |

## Key Rules

1. **Always call `mcp__mtix__mtix_context` before doing any work** — the assembled prompt is your complete briefing
2. Start a session before doing work, end it when done
3. Claim nodes before working on them
4. Follow the state machine — no shortcuts
5. Send heartbeats every 5 minutes to avoid stale detection
6. **Never leave tasks empty** — after `create` or `decompose`, every task MUST have `description`, `prompt`, and `acceptance` populated
7. Add a traceability comment before marking done: task → requirement → test → result
8. No stub implementations — functions must perform their documented purpose end-to-end

## Best Practices for Claude

- **Prefer MCP tools over CLI** when both are available — MCP tools return structured data
- **Batch operations** — use `mcp__mtix__mtix_decompose` instead of multiple `mcp__mtix__mtix_create` calls
- **Search before creating** — use `mcp__mtix__mtix_search` to check for existing similar tasks
- **Progress checks** — use `mcp__mtix__mtix_progress` to verify rollup before reporting completion

## Error Handling

If you encounter an error, check [TROUBLESHOOTING.md](TROUBLESHOOTING.md) for common solutions. If blocked, use `mtix_defer` with a reason rather than abandoning the task. Always document anomalies with `mtix_comment`.
